{{ comp.tabbedCode({ tabs: [
  { label: "Define a service", lang: "ts", code: "import { defineService } from '@netscript/service';\nimport { router } from './router.ts';\n\nconst service = await defineService(router, {\n  name: 'users',\n  port: 3000,\n});" },
  { label: "Install the CLI", lang: "sh", code: "deno install --global --allow-all --name netscript jsr:@netscript/cli/bin\nnetscript init my-app" }
] }) }}

{{ comp.callout({ type: "note" }) }}
NetScript is a backend framework and workspace generator — not a hosted service. You run it on Deno
and own all the generated code.
{{ /comp }}

## Build real systems, not just CRUD

{{ comp.featureGrid({ items: [
  { title: "Contract-first, type-safe", body: "oRPC contracts flow from service to client to UI with no codegen drift. The type checker is your integration test.", href: "/concepts/contracts/" },
  { title: "Durable workflows by design", body: "Sagas, triggers, and jobs are explicit state machines with correlation, persistence, and supervised crash boundaries.", href: "/capabilities/sagas/" },
  { title: "Observable by default", body: "OpenTelemetry tracing and structured logs are wired into jobs, queues, RPC, and SSE from line one.", href: "/concepts/observability/" },
  { title: "Orchestrated with Aspire", body: "One workspace, many resources, a real dashboard — local and deployed. Opt out with --no-aspire.", href: "/concepts/aspire/" },
  { title: "Composable plugins", body: "Add workers, sagas, triggers, and streams in any combination. The host never changes.", href: "/concepts/plugin-model/" },
  { title: "You own your UI", body: "fresh-ui is copy-source: the CLI copies components into your repo. After that, the code is yours.", href: "/capabilities/fresh-ui/" }
] }) }}

